black.content: Yeah, I got a 5. How, you ask? _.

white: Hoping this is all worth it.
Taking AP Psych to boost your GPA.
Worrying about the curve because the exam seemed too easy.
Waiting until July to check your scores online.
Analyzing continuities and changes over time.
Sacrificing someone during the test so everyone else gets a 5.
Mitochondria, the powerhouse of the cell.
Finishing the research paper an hour before the due date.
Having 5 tests on the same day.
The eventual promise of college credit.
